+# Software Test Description (STD)
+
+## Feature: Windows Guest Agent OS/Hostname Info Display
+
+**STP Reference:** [stps/7.md](/home/fedora/thesis/stps/7.md)
+**Jira ID:** [CNV-61262](https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CNV-61262) / [CNV-56888](https://issues.redhat.com/browse/CNV-56888)
+**Generated:** 2026-02-22
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+This STD covers tests for verifying that Windows VM OS version and hostname information are correctly displayed via the QEMU guest agent. The bug fix (CNV-56888) ensures `domain.Status.OSInfo` is not empty when the guest agent is running, resolving a race condition where Windows VMs would incorrectly show "Guest Agent Required" for OS/hostname fields.
+
+Tests verify: correct OS info display, correct hostname display, info persistence after VM reboot, absence of info when guest agent is stopped, and info recovery when the guest agent is started.
+
+---
+
+## Test Files
+
+### File: `tests/virt/guest_agent/test_windows_guest_agent_info.py`
+
+```python
+"""
+Windows Guest Agent OS/Hostname Info Display Tests
+
+STP Reference: stps/7.md
+Jira: CNV-61262, CNV-56888
+
+This module contains tests verifying that Windows VM OS version and hostname
+information are correctly reported via the QEMU guest agent and displayed
+in VMI status. Addresses a race condition where domain.Status.OSInfo was
+sometimes empty despite the guest agent running.
+"""
+
+import pytest
+
+
+class TestWindowsGuestAgentOSInfo:
+    """
+    Tests for Windows VM guest agent OS and hostname information display.
+
+    Markers:
+        - high_resource_vm
+        - tier3
+
+    Preconditions:
+        - Running Windows VM with qemu-guest-agent installed and running
+        - VM is SSH accessible
+    """
+
+    def test_os_info_displayed_in_vmi_status(self):
+        """
+        Test that Windows OS version is correctly displayed in VMI status.
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Query VMI status guestOSInfo and compare with actual Windows OS info
+
+        Expected:
+            - VMI guestOSInfo OS fields match the actual Windows OS information
+        """
+        pass
+
+    def test_hostname_displayed_in_vmi_status(self):
+        """
+        Test that Windows VM hostname is correctly reported by guest agent.
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Query guest agent hostname and compare with actual Windows hostname
+
+        Expected:
+            - Guest agent reported hostname matches the actual Windows hostname
+        """
+        pass
+
+    def test_os_info_persists_after_vm_reboot(self):
+        """
+        Test that guest agent OS info is available after VM reboot.
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Reboot the Windows VM from guest and wait for it to become running and SSH accessible
+            2. Validate guest agent data is consistently available over time
+
+        Expected:
+            - Guest agent data is consistently available after reboot
+        """
+        pass
+
+    def test_no_os_info_without_running_guest_agent(self):
+        """
+        [NEGATIVE] Test that OS info is not available when guest agent service is stopped.
+
+        Preconditions:
+            - qemu-guest-agent service stopped inside the Windows VM
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Query VMI status guestOSInfo
+
+        Expected:
+            - VMI guestOSInfo is empty
+        """
+        pass
+
+    def test_os_info_appears_after_guest_agent_start(self):
+        """
+        Test that OS info becomes available after starting guest agent service.
+
+        Preconditions:
+            - qemu-guest-agent service was previously stopped inside the Windows VM
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Start qemu-guest-agent service inside the Windows VM
+            2. Wait for guest agent to report OS info in VMI status
+
+        Expected:
+            - VMI guestOSInfo contains valid Windows OS information
+        """
+        pass
+
+
+class TestWindowsGuestAgentInfoMultiVersion:
+    """
+    Tests for guest agent OS info display across multiple Windows versions.
+
+    Markers:
+        - high_resource_vm
+        - tier3
+
+    Parametrize:
+        - windows_version: [win10, win2k19, win2k22]
+
+    Preconditions:
+        - Running Windows VM of the parametrized version with qemu-guest-agent installed and running
+        - VM is SSH accessible
+    """
+
+    def test_os_info_correct_for_windows_version(self):
+        """
+        Test that OS info is correctly reported for each supported Windows version.
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Query VMI status guestOSInfo and compare with actual Windows OS info
+
+        Expected:
+            - VMI guestOSInfo OS fields match the actual Windows OS information for the specific version
+        """
+        pass
